<title>FINLAND: Finnish govt, cen bank plan ERM news conference.</title>
<headline>Finnish govt, cen bank plan ERM news conference.</headline>
<dateline>HELSINKI 1996-10-12</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Finnish government and the central bank planned to hold a joint news conference on linking the markka to Europe's exchange rate mechanism (ERM) at 1930/1630 GMT on Saturday, an official told Reuters.</p>
<p>The source, who asked not to be named, spoke as Finnish government ministers assembled at the seat of the government while the European Union's monetary committee in Brussels was meeting to discuss a markka-ERM link.</p>
<p>-- Helsinki newsroom +35 80 6805 0247</p>
